# ChronoLingua - Natural Date Parsing Demo

This is a multi-lingual natural language date parsing application built with:
- React 19
- Next.js 15
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- ShadCN UI
- Sugar.js

When working with this codebase, please follow these guidelines:

1. Code Style:
   - Use TypeScript for all components
   - Follow functional component patterns
   - Use React hooks appropriately
   - Maintain proper type definitions

2. Structure:
   - Keep components small and focused
   - Follow the established directory structure
   - Use ShadCN UI components when available

3. Date Parsing:
   - Use Sugar.js for date parsing and formatting
   - Always set the locale before parsing dates
   - Validate parsed dates before displaying them

4. Styling:
   - Use Tailwind CSS for styling
   - Follow responsive design principles
   - Support both light and dark modes

Note: This project has modern Cursor rules in the .cursor/rules/ directory.
Please refer to those for more detailed guidelines. 